The paper proposes a new scientific contribution ranking index that takes into account the growth degree of research area and variance values of the publication year of cited papers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with information retrieval (cs.IR), data mining (cs.DL), systems and control (cs.SY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
